list-item.p:
Next the team checks to see if it is idle:


If the team is idle and not working on a project it searches within its search range (pRTDetectionRange) to determine if a government asset is found;

If the team is not idle and is currently working on a government asset, it checks to determine if the work is complete.

The asset searches the area around it for other agents:


If the agent found is a terrain agent, then add asset influence to that terrain one time out to a radius of assetInfluenceRange;

If the agent is not terrain, do nothing.

Next, search the area immediately beside the asset for insurgents:


If an insurgent is found then fire a defensive shot at the insurgent;

If no insurgents are found, then do nothing.

The unit searches the area around it for other agents:


If the agent found is an insurgent agent, then determine if there is already an insurgent agent targeted;

If the agent is not an insurgent, do nothing.

Next, determine if a target has been set:


If a target has not been set, then move randomly;

If a target has been set then take a shot.

Search for insurgents around the quick-reaction force. Is insurgent found?


If insurgent is found, then determine if another insurgent is already targeted;

If no insurgent is found, go home.

